  "Cartograms are inaccurate and should not be used, which represents a common but incomplete view of how these appear dynamics operate": "",
  "Japan is geographically larger than Russia, since standard models of appear behavior predict this outcome under normal conditions": "",
  "Cartograms powerfully communicate statistical data by replacing geographic size with data values. Japan's small territory but large economy makes it appear much bigger, while Russia's vast territory but smaller economy makes it appear reduced.": "",
  "A geographer creates a choropleth map showing poverty rates by county in a state. Critics point out that two counties with identical poverty rates but very different populations receive the same shading. What limitation of choropleth maps does this highlight?": "",
