  "Choropleth maps should only show one county at a time regardless of prevailing conditions in practice": "",
  "A limitation of choropleth maps is that they shade entire areas uniformly based on rates or averages, regardless of population size. A huge rural county with few people gets the same visual emphasis as a small densely populated county.": "",
  "Some scholars argue that the widespread use of the Mercator projection in classrooms has contributed to Eurocentric worldviews because Europe appears larger and more centrally positioned than it actually is. How can map projections influence perceptions of the world?": "",
