  "The Mercator projection's conformal property means that angles are preserved everywhere, so a straight line (rhumb line) represents a path of constant compass bearing. This allowed sailors to plot a course and follow it using only a compass.": "",
  "A researcher maps COVID-19 cases using two different approaches: total cases per country (proportional symbol map) and cases per 100,000 people per country (choropleth map). The United States appears as a major hotspot on the first map but appears moderate on the second. Why do these maps tell different stories?": "",
